data.value:
Bordeaux is the city that gives its name to world-famous wines. It is located in the Gironde section of the Aquitaine region in southwestern France. Bordeaux, a historic port city, is located on the Garonne River. It stands out with its splendid architecture, historical buildings, vibrant city life and a leading culture-art environment.
In the center of the city there are more than three hundred and fifty historical buildings and monuments. The majestic bir Quinconces ”square is perfect for a romantic stroll. The Place de la Bourse, the Grand Theater de Bordeaux, the Bordeaux Cathedral and the Aquitaine Museum are all on top of this list. It is possible to complete a visit to the city of Bordeaux with the surrounding vineyards and the famous Dordogne area, famous for its picturesque countryside and castles.
